!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

away /əˈweɪ/

1. ADV If someone or something moves or is moved away from a place, they move or are moved so that they are no longer there. If you are away from a place, you are not in the place where people expect you to be. 离开 

例： An injured policeman was led away by colleagues. 一位受伤的警察被同事们带走了。 

例： He walked away from his car. 他从他的车边走开了。 

例： Jason was away on a business trip. 贾森出差在外。 

2. ADV If you look or turn away from something, you move your head so that you are no longer looking at it. (目光) 移开地 

例： She quickly looked away and stared down at her hands. 她迅速转移目光，低头盯着自己的双手。 

3. ADV If you put something away , you put it where it should be. If you hide someone or something away , you put them in a place where nobody can see them or find them. (收藏) 好 [ADV after v] 

例： I put my journal away and prepared for bed. 我把日记收好，准备睡觉。 

例： All her letters were carefully filed away in folders. 她所有的信件都被仔细地归档在文件夹里。 

4. ADV You use away to talk about future events. For example, if an event is a week away , it will happen after a week. 距离 (某事件的时间) ['be' amount ADV] 

例： ...the Washington summit, now only just over two weeks away. …现在离华盛顿峰会的召开只有两个多星期。 

5. ADV When a sports team plays away , it plays on its opponents' playing court or field. (比赛) 在客场地 [ADV after v] 

例： ...a sensational 4-3 victory for the team playing away. …该队在客场4-3轰动性的胜利。 

6. ADJ Away is also an adjective. 客场的 [ADJ n] 

例： Pittsburgh is about to play an important away game. 匹兹堡队将要打一场重要的客场比赛。 

7. ADV You can use away to say that something slowly disappears, becomes less significant, or changes so that it is no longer the same. 渐逝地 [ADV after v] 

例： So much snow has already melted away. 那么多雪已经逐渐融化掉了。 

例： His voice died away in a whisper. 他的声音渐渐放低成了耳语。 

8. ADV You use away to show that there has been a change or development from one state or situation to another. 变化发展地 

例： British courts are increasingly moving away from sending young offenders to prison. 英国法庭逐渐地不再将犯法的年轻人送进监狱。 

9. ADV You can use away to emphasize a continuous or repeated action. 持续不断地 [ADV after v] [强调] 

例： He would often be working away on his word processor late into the night. 他经常会在他的文字处理机上持续工作到深夜。 

10. ADV You use away to show that something is removed. 拿走 [ADV after v] 

例： If you take my work away I can't be happy anymore. 如果你带走了我的工作，那我就再也高兴不起来了。 

11. PHRASE If something is away from a person or place, it is at a distance from that person or place. 离 (某人或某地) 一段距离 

例： The two women were sitting as far away from each other as possible. 那两个女人坐得离对方尽可能地远。 

12. right away→see right

